President Obama has declared a major disaster in the U.S. Virgin Islands due to severe storms, flooding, rockslides, and mudslides caused by Tropical Storm Tomas. Federal aid will be provided to supplement recovery efforts in the affected area, specifically on the island of St. Croix. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Philip E. Parr has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Additional designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA.